column2: No particles.  Reading taken after 4 days of hard- intermittant rains.

Lake turned in late July.  6 weeks earlier than 2008-09.  In 2005 lake turned in June.  Scummy surface covered shoreline to 30 feet out during last three weeks.  Now no longer appears.  New areas of lily pads and arrowhead appearing along southern and western shores.
Small green particles.  Reading done 4 days after 4 inches of rainfall.
Small green particles-very dense.  Reading after 10 days higher than normal temperature during the day- 60 to 75 degrees.
water level up ~ 2 " from fall 2010. Ice out about 4/20/2011
cloudy/rainy day. Hydrologist testing due to dense particulate condition
water level within 4" of old high water mark on shoreline rocks
hot- humid for last 10 days- late day t-stroms with wind. fine yellow particulate
fine particulates- no rain in 7 days- lillies and cattails present - no arrowhead this year
fine particulates- day temp. 60 degrees F- nights 40 degrees F in past 7 days  more than 1" rain in 7 days
fine particulates- previous week temp. 65-75 degrees during days- 45-50 degrees during nights- no rain in 7 days
few particles. Some floating algae and aquatic plants.
level down three inches from 2011. No algae- few particles.
Small particles.  Lake level ~6" below historic high water mark.
Ice out 4/23/13. No turnover this year.  cattails few due to muskrats needing forage longer this year 11/18/13
